Therefore, $Q(-5,0)$ and $R(-2,0)$.

Step 2: Calculate the area of triangle $PQR$.
The base of the triangle $PQR$ is $QR$, which is equal to the difference in $x$-coordinates of $R$ and $Q$: $\text{base} = |x_R - x_Q| = |-2 - (-5)| = 3$.

